msgid "``list_job_snapshots()`` returns current jobs plus retained terminal history. ``get_job_snapshot(job_id)`` returns one snapshot or ``None``. ``rescale_operator(job_id, operator_id, parallelism, timeout=60)`` performs a local, barrier-aligned parallelism change when the operator supports it and returns a JSON-safe operation result whose status is ``COMPLETED``, ``NOOP``, ``REJECTED``, or ``FAILED``. The first version does not resize source operators, transactional sinks, collecting sinks, or lifecycle classes that have not explicitly opted into concurrent runtime handoff. Parallel and multiple source operators are supported when rescaling a downstream operator; their post-commit recovery point uses one shared, direct-input-aligned checkpoint epoch. See :doc:`../operator-rescaling` for prerequisites, result handling, state migration, and the stabilization checkpoint. ``cancel_job(job_id, timeout=60)`` addresses a published job by job ID, while the CLI ``stop`` command addresses its Ray namespace."
msgstr "``list_job_snapshots()`` 返回当前作业及保留的终态历史；``get_job_snapshot(job_id)`` 返回一个快照或 ``None``。算子支持时，``rescale_operator(job_id, operator_id, parallelism, timeout=60)`` 会执行局部且与屏障对齐的并行度调整，并返回可安全进行 JSON 序列化的操作结果，其状态为 ``COMPLETED``、``NOOP``、``REJECTED`` 或 ``FAILED``。首个版本不调整源算子、事务型 Sink、收集型 Sink，以及未明确选择并发运行时切换的生命周期类。调整下游算子时支持并行源算子和多个源算子；提交后的恢复点使用一个共享且与直接输入对齐的检查点轮次。有关前置条件、结果处理、状态迁移和稳定化检查点，请参阅 :doc:`../operator-rescaling`。``cancel_job(job_id, timeout=60)`` 按作业 ID 定位已发布作业，而 CLI 的 ``stop`` 命令按 Ray 命名空间定位。"
